landmarks.name: Schiefe Brücke (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the Schiefe Brücke (Baden), a bridge over a river, with buildings and a hillside in the background.

landmarks.name: Hochbrücke (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a high-angle shot of Baden, Switzerland, featuring the Hochbrücke bridge, colorful buildings, and the Limmat River.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This is a wide shot of the Hochbrücke bridge in Baden, Switzerland, with the old town, church, and castle visible in the background.

landmarks.name: Reformierte Kirche Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of the Reformierte Kirche Baden, a white church with a dark roof and a golden spire, set against a clear blue sky.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the upper portion of the Reformierte Kirche Baden, a white church with a dark dome and spire, set against a blue sky.

landmarks.name: Stadtpfarrkirche Maria Himmelfahrt (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a photo of the Stadtpfarrkirche Maria Himmelfahrt (Baden), showing its tower and part of the main building.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This is a photo of the Stadtpfarrkirche Maria Himmelfahrt church in Baden, Switzerland, surrounded by other buildings and trees.

landmarks.name: Stadtturm (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The Stadtturm (Baden) is shown in a street view, with other buildings and a fountain visible.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This is a photo of the Stadtturm (Baden), a tall clock tower in a town square, surrounded by buildings and people.

landmarks.name: Landvogteischloss Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a photo of the Landvogteischloss Baden, a castle in Baden, Switzerland, with a covered bridge connecting to it.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This photo shows the Landvogteischloss Baden, a castle connected to a covered bridge over a river.

landmarks.name: Sankt-Nikolaus-Kapelle (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The Sankt-Nikolaus-Kapelle in Baden is shown atop a rocky hill with a Swiss flag waving from a tower.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the Sankt-Nikolaus-Kapelle (Baden), a small chapel with a bell tower, partially obscured by tree branches.

landmarks.name: Holzbrücke (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the Holzbrücke (wooden bridge) and a medieval tower in Baden, Switzerland, spanning a river.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This photo shows the Holzbrücke (wooden bridge) in Baden, Switzerland, connecting a building to the other side of the Limmat river.

landmarks.name: Ruine Stein
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the Ruine Stein, a castle ruin with a flag on top, situated on a hill with a church and surrounded by trees.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the ruins of Stein Castle, with a stone tower and walls overgrown with vegetation, set against a cloudy sky.

landmarks.name: Historisches Museum Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the Historisches Museum Baden, featuring a tower and a covered bridge over a river, with a cityscape in the background.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the Historisches Museum Baden, a tall building connected to a covered bridge with round windows, situated next to a river.

landmarks.name: Museum Langmatt
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a photo of the exterior of Museum Langmatt, a large house with a red tile roof, white walls, and green shutters, surrounded by a green lawn and trees.

landmarks.name: Haus zum Schwert (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of Haus zum Schwert in Baden, Switzerland, a white building with grey shutters and a decorative balcony.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the exterior of Haus zum Schwert in Baden, Switzerland, a large building with many windows and a distinctive roof.

landmarks.name: Synagoge (Baden AG)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of the Synagogue in Baden, Switzerland, featuring its distinctive architecture and a Star of David on top.

landmarks.name: Hotel zum wilden Mann
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the entrance to the "Gasthof zum Wilden Mann" with its sign, coat of arms, and lamps.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the exterior of "Hotel zum wilden Mann" in a narrow alleyway, with outdoor seating and architectural details.

landmarks.name: Inhalatorium (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of the Inhalatorium building in Baden, Switzerland, featuring a symmetrical facade with windows, a central door, and a triangular pediment.

landmarks.name: St.-Anna-Kapelle (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: This photo shows the St.-Anna-Kapelle in Baden, a building with a distinctive red tile roof and a simple, somewhat austere facade.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the St.-Anna-Kapelle in Baden, Switzerland, from a side angle, partially obscured by greenery.

landmarks.name: Bahnhof Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a photo of the Baden train station, a yellow and white building with green shutters and a distinctive architectural style.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the train platform at Bahnhof Baden with a train, people, and architectural details of the station.

landmarks.name: Schlossberg (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: This photo shows Schlossberg castle on a hill overlooking the town of Baden, Switzerland, with a bridge and church spires visible.

landmarks.name: Aquae Helveticae
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a scenic view of Baden, Switzerland, showcasing its historic buildings, including churches and a covered bridge, nestled along the river.

landmarks.name: Kurpark (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows a statue and fountain in Kurpark, Baden, with a woman figure on top and other figures around the base.

landmarks.name: Kurtheater Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of the Kurtheater Baden, a modern building with large glass windows and a unique architectural design.

landmarks.name: Kapuzinerkloster Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the Kapuzinerkloster Baden, a large building complex with a church featuring red spires, set against a clear blue sky.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This is an aerial view of the Kapuzinerkloster Baden, a large building with a distinctive roof and a street with cars alongside.

landmarks.name: Stadtbibliothek Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a clear, well-lit photograph of the Stadtbibliothek Baden, a building with unique architectural features including a turret and half-timbered gable.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows the exterior of the Stadtbibliothek Baden, a multi-story building with a distinctive architectural style and some snow on the roof.

landmarks.name: Schulhausplatz (Baden)
landmarks.photoDescription: This is a high-angle view of a street in Baden, Switzerland, showing buildings, traffic, and a hillside in the background.
landmarks.photoDescription2: This is an aerial view of Schulhausplatz in Baden, Switzerland, showing buildings, a road with traffic, and surrounding greenery.

landmarks.name: Schweizer Kindermuseum
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of the Schweizer Kindermuseum, a large white building with a lawn in front.
landmarks.photoDescription2: The photo shows children and an adult playing a game inside the Schweizer Kindermuseum, with posters visible on the wall behind them.

landmarks.name: Wettingen railway station
landmarks.photoDescription: This is an exterior shot of the Wettingen railway station, a building with a distinctive architectural style.

landmarks.name: Kantonsschule Baden
landmarks.photoDescription: The photo shows the exterior of Kantonsschule Baden, a modern building with a glass facade, a sculpture, and a grassy lawn in front.
